column5: Thanks all for input. Will see what it looks like next Friday. Sure they are blasting north on 61 somewhere anyways You all drive safe.
Proud as Punch seems to never go away
Mr. Ranger let us know how 61 is also. I saw on the website there was alittle construction by twin ports I believe. I'll be heading that way in a month. Thanks
Coming up 35N from Minneapolis is there any screwed up detour to connect to H wy61?

We went through Duluth on June 24 at noon. Followed the detour signs. Other than waiting for a train no issues. Came home on July 2 at noon. 53 exit east was closed and detour took us to Hwy 2 Bong Bridge. No delays again. MAJOR redo of the whole interchange. Will be nice when it's done. Travel safe.

As of my two trips in mid to late June no issues. There was a little construction on 35 closer to the cities but only slowed us a little bit traveling up on a Wednesday morning. No issues in Duluth going from 35 to 61. They are doing lots of work but there are 2 lanes each direction so no big deal. 61 there are a couple of construction zones east of Two Harbors. One around Betty’s Pies and another one east a bit. No issues although towing a boat through there isn’t a real treat with lots of oncoming traffic.
They are resurfacing but they have a crossover so it will be fine.

Having lost our last three trips to Canada I missed the fact that the major interchange in Duluth with 53 and I35 is doing a three year make over. Badly needed. We leave next week Friday from Wausau, WI to Nakina ON. I see Google has a detour going both ways via Garfield Ave in Duluth. Another note I saw suggested taking the Bong Bridge over then north on I35. Just curious if anyone has gone this way in the past 30 days and any suggestions. Thanks

I went thorough there both ways a couple of weeks ago. Going north, I got off of 53 and followed 2 through Superior across the Bong to I believe 35 briefly to 2, then to 33, and back to 53. Same coming home. I tow a small camper trailer, and the Blaknik bridge on 53 always gives me the willies anyway - I'll be taking the Bong in the future, construction of not. I'm not saying it's any shorter, but I liked it. Hint - coming south on 53, be careful not to turn prematurely onto 33, unless you'd like a scenic tour of St. Louis Cty backroads;-)
LOL on the good tip. Appreciate the insight and will keep that as a solid plan. Glad you made is safely my friend.
The Bong is the way to go.
I went through there last weekend, no issues following the detour signs.

I also drove up last week from Wausau, WI. I followed the detour without any issues, and got through the cities promptly. On the return trip this past Sunday, my navigation unit wanted me to turn quite a bit earlier, but I just followed the detour signs again without any problems!
Have fun, Jerry, say hello to Bob (and Shelly) for me! Bill
Will do Bill. Miss ya Buddy.
We came back 2 weeks ago. One vehicle took one route. The second rig took the other. We both arrived at Gronks for lunch about the same time.
